Scientists at NASA and NOAA, the
National Oceanic and Atmospheric

01:52.312 --> 01:56.383 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
Administration,
reported that today.

01:56.383 --> 02:02.456 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As this NASA animation shows,
the data show a steady
accumulation of heat in recent
decades.

02:02.456 --> 02:06.560 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the researchers say it
should make doubters of climate
change think twice.

02:06.560 --> 02:12.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
COMPTON TUCKER, NASA: Fifteen of
the past 16 years have been the
warmest years on record.

02:12.666 --> 02:17.738 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
