killed more than 150 people,
mostly children and teachers.

04:33.373 --> 04:37.444 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TIM CRAIG: Since then, the army
has really sort of stepped up
its response to this menace

04:37.444 --> 04:41.748 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and this threat. And terrorism
attacks went way down this year,
depending on what study

04:41.748 --> 04:45.919 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
you are looking at, 50 percent
down, 70 percent down.

04:45.919 --> 04:50.056 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But clearly, as a resident of
Pakistan at the moment, I can
say it's a much safer place.

04:50.056 --> 04:56.029 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
With that said, as everyone
around the world knows, it only
takes one time for a terrorist

04:56.029 --> 04:59.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to be able to enter a location
to carry out a horrific attack.

04:59.966 --> 05:04.771 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: After today's
attack, Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif vowed again to

05:04.771 --> 05:09.643 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
