more questions, and more delays
than any visitors to the United

07:18.271 --> 07:21.341 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
States from any other country.

07:21.341 --> 07:25.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEN. JOHN CORNYN (R), Texas:
What this legislation is about,
though, is about national
security,

07:25.679 --> 07:31.951 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
people who are refugees, whether
they're adequately vetted by the
appropriate authorities before

07:31.951 --> 07:34.421 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they come to the United States
and live in our communities.
This is not about banning

07:34.421 --> 07:36.656 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
refugees.

07:36.656 --> 07:42.662 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The bill cleared the
Republican-led House last fall
with a veto-proof majority.

07:42.662 --> 07:48.535 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
