black city has been in an
economic tailspin for decades,

11:43.937 --> 11:47.240 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ever since General Motors cut
production here. Forty percent
of Flint's 100,000 residents

11:47.240 --> 11:51.044 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
live in poverty.

11:51.044 --> 11:55.515 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In 2011, Governor Rick Snyder
turned near total control of
Flint over to a series of

11:55.515 --> 11:59.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
emergency managers. They began
major cost-cutting, including a
decision to try and save $5
million

11:59.986 --> 12:03.856 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
by switching Flint's
water supply.

12:03.856 --> 12:07.760 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Officials decided said they
wanted to get water from Lake
Huron, which is 80 miles to

12:07.760 --> 12:11.297 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the east of us, but that
pipeline wasn't going to be
finished for two more years. And
so,

12:11.297 --> 12:12.865 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the interim, they decided
they were going to get their
water from right here, from the

12:12.865 --> 12:16.135 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Flint River.

12:16.135 --> 12:21.374 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But as soon as the riverwater
began flowing into Flint in
April of 2014, red flags popped

12:21.374 --> 12:26.312 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
up. The water smelled bad, and
it flowed in a startling array
of colors. E. coli and other

12:26.312 --> 12:31.451 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
bacteria were discovered,
followed by chemicals that can
cause liver and kidney problems.

12:31.451 --> 12:35.021 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the fall of 2014, the local
GM plant stopped using Flint
water because it was corroding

12:35.021 --> 12:37.423 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
their auto parts.

12:37.423 --> 12:40.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RHONDA KELSO, Flint Resident: I
mean, you can see the
particulates in it. See it
floating?

12:40.593 --> 12:43.229 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
See the brown stuff in it?

12:43.229 --> 12:45.231 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Yes. Yes.

12:45.231 --> 12:49.135 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
RHONDA KELSO: Yes, that's in
our -- my daughter's body.

12:49.135 --> 12:53.806 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Lifetime Flint
resident Rhonda Kelso, like
thousands of other residents,

12:53.806 --> 12:58.811 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
soon discovered there was also
poisonous lead in the water. The
whole problem occurred because

12:58.811 --> 13:03.850 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Flint River corroded the
city's old lead pipes, leaching
the toxic metal into the water

13:03.850 --> 13:07.920 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
supply. Kelso's 12-year-old
daughter, Kaylynn (ph), who's
already developmentally delayed

13:07.920 --> 13:12.258 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and hearing impaired, has now
tested positive for lead in her
blood.

13:12.258 --> 13:18.364 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RHONDA KELSO: They kept telling
us something was safe, and it
was revealed that it wasn't

13:18.364 --> 13:24.671 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
safe. We had to rely on outside
agencies to let us know that the
water was poison. And

13:24.671 --> 13:28.207 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
we already knew it was,
but we had to prove it.

13:28.207 --> 13:32.545 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: One of the
people who helped prove it was
one of Kaylynn's doctors, Dr.

13:32.545 --> 13:35.715 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mona Hanna-Attisha. She's the
director of the pediatric
residency program at Hurley

13:35.715 --> 13:38.484 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Medical Center in Flint.

13:38.484 --> 13:41.788 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. MONA HANNA-ATTISHA, Hurley
Medical Center: When
pediatricians hear anything
about lead,

13:41.788 --> 13:45.792 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we stand up straight and we
freak out, because we know lead.
And lead is a potent, known,

13:45.792 --> 13:48.394 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
irreversible neurotoxin.

13:48.394 --> 13:53.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Late last
summer, Dr. Hanna-Attisha tried
to get county and state data on
how

13:53.366 --> 13:58.438 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
much lead Flint's kids had been
absorbing into their blood, but
she hit roadblocks.

13:58.438 --> 14:03.943 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So she then pulled data on
roughly 1,700 kids from her own
hospital and other local
pediatricians.

14:03.943 --> 14:07.346 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. MONA HANNA-ATTISHA: We
didn't sleep. We did this right
away. This was the fastest

14:07.346 --> 14:11.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
research project I have ever
done, because of kind of the
public health community
implications.

14:11.384 --> 14:16.556 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There was one neighborhood, one
specific ward of a city where
the percentage of lead poisoning

14:16.556 --> 14:20.793 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
actually tripled. It went from
about 5 percent of kids to over
almost 16 percent of kids

14:20.793 --> 14:24.163 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
who were tested who had
elevated blood lead levels.

14:24.163 --> 14:26.599 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: She released
her findings at a news
conference last September, but
her

14:26.599 --> 14:29.368 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
data was dismissed by
state health officials.

14:29.368 --> 14:31.838 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. MONA HANNA-ATTISHA: We were
attacked. So, we were told that
we were unfortunate

14:31.838 --> 14:32.905 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
researchers, that we were...

14:32.905 --> 14:34.407 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Unfortunate?

14:34.407 --> 14:37.343 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
DR. MONA HANNA-ATTISHA:
Unfortunate researchers, that we
were causing near-hysteria.

14:37.343 --> 14:43.316 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: But two weeks
later, officials acknowledged
her findings were correct. And,

14:43.316 --> 14:45.952 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
separately, researchers at
Virginia Tech had also confirmed
high levels of lead in Flint's

14:45.952 --> 14:48.454 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
water.

14:48.454 --> 14:53.259 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This contamination could've been
avoided if officials had only
added an anti-corrosion

14:53.259 --> 14:56.929 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
agent to the water. In fact,
federal law requires it. But
they didn't do it in Flint, and
no

14:56.929 --> 15:00.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
one has fully explained why.

15:00.133 --> 15:03.136 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DR. LAWRENCE REYNOLDS,
President, Mott Children's
Health Center: It's something
that no parent

15:03.136 --> 15:08.007 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
would accept. It's something no
city, county, or state
government should accept. And
there's

15:08.007 --> 15:10.543 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
no way it can be justified.

15:10.543 --> 15:14.981 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Dr. Lawrence
Reynolds is a pediatrician and
president of Mott Children's

15:14.981 --> 15:19.986 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Health Center. He says lead
causes a litany of problems for
kids, among them, delayed

15:19.986 --> 15:23.990 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
mental development,
irritability, aggression and
learning problems.

15:23.990 --> 15:29.462 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. LAWRENCE REYNOLDS: If you
have seen those I.Q. curves
where there's the big hump and

15:29.462 --> 15:36.469 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the small tails, 5 percent on
either end, what lead exposure
does is it shifts the curve

15:36.469 --> 15:44.377 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the lower I.Q. score, so we
will have more kids with lower
I.Q. and perhaps more children

15:44.377 --> 15:49.715 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who will have learning problems
and require services. But then
start multiplying these

15:49.715 --> 15:55.254 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
things by thousands and imagine
what a school district has to
deal with.

15:55.254 --> 15:56.756 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAREN WEAVER, Mayor of Flint,
Michigan: We're talking about a
whole generation of 5 and

15:56.756 --> 15:58.491 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
under.

15:58.491 --> 16:03.596 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Newly elected
Mayor Karen Weaver campaigned on
fixing the water crisis,

16:03.596 --> 16:07.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and shortly after taking office
and with limited powers, she
declared a state of emergency,

16:07.333 --> 16:09.969 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
trying to get her
city some help.

16:09.969 --> 16:13.706 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAREN WEAVER: People said that
was something that couldn't be
done, but I said that let

16:13.706 --> 16:19.612 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
them tell us no. Let them tell
the people of Flint that we
don't deserve these financial

16:19.612 --> 16:23.349 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
resources, these supports and
these services for our families.

16:23.349 --> 16:28.888 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KIM STREBY: We don't live in
Third World conditions, where we
should have safe drinking water,

16:28.888 --> 16:30.923 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and we don't.

16:30.923 --> 16:35.661 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Kim Streby's
two sons are Ronan, who's 13,
and Jude, who's 11. He's

16:35.661 --> 16:39.832 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the one whose blood test came
back with elevated lead levels.

16:39.832 --> 16:42.301 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So you guys had been drinking
with it, cooking with it,
brushing your teeth in it,
taking

16:42.301 --> 16:44.070 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
baths in it, 100 percent?

16:44.070 --> 16:46.038 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
RONAN STREBY, Flint
Resident: Yes.

16:46.038 --> 16:47.607 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: And then when
you found out that there was
something wrong with that

16:47.607 --> 16:50.142 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
water, how did you
feel about that?

16:50.142 --> 16:54.747 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RONAN STREBY: I felt kind of
scared, like, to know that I was
using this water for pretty

16:54.747 --> 16:57.116 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
much everything, and then I
found out that it could be
dangerous.

16:57.116 --> 17:03.623 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDE STREBY, Flint Resident: I
was kind of grossed out, because
imagine you drinking

17:03.623 --> 17:10.596 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
water for a year and knowing
that there's something that can
be life-threatening.

17:10.596 --> 17:14.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: As a parent, I
couldn't imagine the feeling
that for over a year-and-a-half

17:14.934 --> 17:19.405 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
my kids were drinking water that
somebody should've known was
poisonous.

17:19.405 --> 17:30.049 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KIM STREBY: There are no words.
I don't know what to say. It's
anger, frustration. And

17:30.049 --> 17:32.318 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
you wonder what's next.

17:32.318 --> 17:36.055 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: At least three
different class-action lawsuits
have now been filed,

17:36.055 --> 17:43.829 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
blaming local and state
officials, even the governor,
for negligence.

17:43.829 --> 17:47.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Last night in Lansing, a crowd
gathered outside the capital,
demanding Governor Rick Snyder

17:47.767 --> 17:52.939 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
resign for his role in the
crisis. Inside, Snyder focused
his speech on Flint and pledged

17:52.939 --> 17:56.142 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
state officials would do all
they could to fix the problem.

17:56.142 --> 18:02.415 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GOV. RICK SNYDER: No citizen of
this great state should endure
this kind of catastrophe.

18:02.415 --> 18:06.786 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Government failed you, federal,
state and local leaders, by
breaking the trust you placed

18:06.786 --> 18:09.088 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
in us.

18:09.088 --> 18:12.525 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: But those
assurances aren't enough for
Rhonda Kelso. She's signed on to

18:12.525 --> 18:14.927 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
one of those
class-action lawsuits.

18:14.927 --> 18:18.497 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RHONDA KELSO: Oh, they think
that we're a permanent
underclass and they think that
we're

18:18.497 --> 18:26.973 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
uneducated and ignorant and that
we are the most violent city in
America, and people want

18:26.973 --> 18:30.042 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to dispose of people like that.

18:30.042 --> 18:33.512 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Flint, as you
know, is a majority black
community, and when we look

18:33.512 --> 18:37.483 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at who is exposed to lead around
the country, those are also
majority black communities.

18:37.483 --> 18:39.485 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DR. LAWRENCE REYNOLDS: Yes.

18:39.485 --> 18:42.421 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Do you think
that that's part of what's also
going on here?

18:42.421 --> 18:48.861 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. LAWRENCE REYNOLDS: Speaking
to me, as a person of color and
as a resident of the

18:48.861 --> 18:55.701 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
city of Flint, I will ask the
other question: If this were a
Grand Blanc, Michigan,
Bloomfield

18:55.701 --> 19:01.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hills, St. Joseph, Michigan,
which are mostly white,
middle-class, would we have had
the

19:01.941 --> 19:05.511 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
same response if there
was a water issue?

19:05.511 --> 19:08.781 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: And
what do you think?

19:08.781 --> 19:13.285 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. LAWRENCE REYNOLDS: There
would've been a completely
different response. It would

19:13.285 --> 19:19.025 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
have been a more timely
response, and those complaints
would've been taken as
legitimate.

19:19.025 --> 19:23.162 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The city of
Flint has stopped using the
Flint River as its source, and
corrosion

19:23.162 --> 19:27.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
control is now being used.
People from across the United
States have been donating tens

19:27.666 --> 19:30.102 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of thousands of bottles of
water, and more National Guard
troops have arrived to help

19:30.102 --> 19:32.238 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
distribute them.

19:32.238 --> 19:37.443 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KIM STREBY: I love this city and
I love the people in this city
and it's a great city.

19:37.443 --> 19:46.152 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And this water situation is just
absolutely devastating to me,
but it isn't the definition

19:46.152 --> 19:48.054 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of the city.

19:48.054 --> 19:49.922 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Flint's
better than that.

19:49.922 --> 19:52.625 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
KIM STREBY: Absolutely.
Absolutely.

19:52.625 --> 20:03.702 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: For the "PBS
NewsHour," I'm William Brangham
in Flint, Michigan.

20:03.702 --> 20:18.517 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Next: growing
concerns over a mosquito-borne
virus that is linked with

20:18.517 --> 20:23.823 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
birth defects and has moved into
South America, the Caribbean and
now the U.S. And, so far,

20:23.823 --> 20:25.558 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
there's no treatment
for the virus.

20:25.558 --> 20:28.260 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown has the story.

20:28.260 --> 20:33.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The Zika virus
has been known of for decades.
But beginning last May in

20:33.466 --> 20:39.438 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Brazil, it's taken a frightening
turn, being linked for the first
time to babies born with

20:39.438 --> 20:46.011 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
unusually small heads and brain
damage, more than 3,800 cases to
date.

20:46.011 --> 20:50.015 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Zika is transmitted by
mosquitoes. And government
workers have been checking house
to house

20:50.015 --> 20:52.885 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in Brazil for breeding grounds.

20:52.885 --> 20:56.755 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCELO CASTRO, Health Minister
of Brazil (through translator):
We are in this battle,

20:56.755 --> 21:00.559 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
this fight to do this
in a record time.

21:00.559 --> 21:05.865 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: In most cases,
individuals who contract the
virus show few or no symptoms.

21:05.865 --> 21:10.936 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the virus is spreading,
already to a number of countries
and territories in South and

21:10.936 --> 21:13.873 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Central America and
the Caribbean.

21:13.873 --> 21:19.645 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There have also been a handful
of positive tests confirmed in
the U.S. In each of these

21:19.645 --> 21:23.516 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
cases, the patient or mother is
believed to have picked up the
virus abroad.

21:23.516 --> 21:27.153 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STEVE HUARD, Florida Health
Department: The individual went
to the doctor, had known about

21:27.153 --> 21:31.023 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Zika virus, let their
physician know that they were in
an area that had it. They
tested,

21:31.023 --> 21:32.658 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and came back positive.

21:32.658 --> 21:39.665 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The CDC recently
issued an advisory recommending
that pregnant women

21:39.665 --> 21:44.803 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
avoid travel to affected areas
and says those who have already
traveled to such areas and

21:44.803 --> 21:48.507 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
are feeling sick should
be tested for infection.

21:48.507 --> 21:53.712 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I spoke about all this yesterday
with CDC Director Dr. Thomas
Frieden, and asked first

21:53.712 --> 21:56.882 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
how serious a threat he
sees in the Zika virus.

21:56.882 --> 21:59.351 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. THOMAS FRIEDEN, Director,
Centers for Disease Control and
Prevention: Zika is really

21:59.351 --> 22:06.325 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
new in this form, although it's
been around, known since 1947.
It's only in the past eight

22:06.325 --> 22:11.530 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
or nine years that we have seen
outbreaks of Zika, and only in
the past couple of months

22:11.530 --> 22:17.336 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that we have seen this large
number of cases of a serious
birth defect in Brazil which

22:17.336 --> 22:20.873 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
appears to be related to Zika.

22:20.873 --> 22:25.511 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's why we're recommending
that if you're pregnant and
you're thinking about travel,

22:25.511 --> 22:30.716 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
check the CDC Web site to think
about whether you want to go to
that place or not.

22:30.716 --> 22:35.287 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You're telling
people right now, pregnant
women, to think about
postponing.

22:35.287 --> 22:38.857 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You're not definitively saying
don't travel to these countries
yet?

22:38.857 --> 22:44.096 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. THOMAS FRIEDEN: We're
advising pregnant women not to
travel to places that have Zika

22:44.096 --> 22:47.099 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
transmission, because there is
just too much we don't know, so
if it's possible to avoid

22:47.099 --> 22:51.203 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that travel, that's
important to do.

22:51.203 --> 22:56.709 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For anyone who is in an area
with Zika, pregnant or not, or
if a pregnant woman goes to a
place

22:56.709 --> 23:02.147 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
or is in a place that may have
Zika virus spreading, it's
spread by mosquitoes, and

23:02.147 --> 23:07.586 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
there are important things you
can do to reduce your risk of
getting a mosquito bite. You

23:07.586 --> 23:11.790 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
can wear repellent. That works.
You have to wear it all day
long, because these are
mosquitoes

23:11.790 --> 23:14.827 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that bite during the day.

23:14.827 --> 23:20.165 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You can also wear clothing that
has permethrin in it. These are
both safe in pregnancy. You

23:20.165 --> 23:26.038 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
can wear long sleeves and long
pants to reduce your exposure,
and you can stay inside in

23:26.038 --> 23:30.576 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
air conditioning or screened
spaces. All of these things
really do reduce your risk of

23:30.576 --> 23:36.115 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
mosquito bites. But we are
recommending at this point,
until we know more, just to be

23:36.115 --> 23:42.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
safer, that pregnant women, if
possible, avoid travel to places
that have Zika virus
transmission.

23:42.521 --> 23:44.089 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Now, you have
said several times there's too
much -- there is a lot we

23:44.089 --> 23:47.092 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
just don't know.

23:47.092 --> 23:52.965 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Let's just go through what we
don't, what we do know, because
I gather that, until recently,

23:52.965 --> 23:57.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
most cases involving Zika were
not very -- considered very
dangerous, right? Many of them
had no

23:57.469 --> 23:58.737 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
symptoms whatsoever.

23:58.737 --> 24:01.807 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DR. THOMAS FRIEDEN: Absolutely.

24:01.807 --> 24:07.046 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have generally seen as many
as four out of five people who
get infected by Zika don't

24:07.046 --> 24:11.417 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
know it. They don't have any
symptoms. And among those who
get infected, the symptoms

24:11.417 --> 24:16.989 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
tend to be mild and go away
within about a week, a rash and
fever and not feeling well.

24:16.989 --> 24:22.661 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have seen some reports of
people who may have weakness or
paralysis temporarily after

24:22.661 --> 24:27.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Zika. Whether that's related or
not, we still don't know. That's
being investigated. But

24:27.566 --> 24:31.270 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what's really concerning is this
large number of birth defects
that have been identified

24:31.270 --> 24:33.405 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in Brazil.

24:33.405 --> 24:39.878 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And studies in our CDC lab have
identified that, in some of the
infants and some of the

24:39.878 --> 24:45.084 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
miscarried fetuses, because
there were miscarriages, we have
identified the Zika virus. That
doesn't

24:45.084 --> 24:50.055 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
say that it's the only cause or
the cause of all of them. There
may be other factors,

24:50.055 --> 24:55.227 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
nutritional or other infections,
that are going into that, but
this is a very unusual

24:55.227 --> 25:01.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
circumstance. It's very unusual
that we identify a new virus
that causes serious birth
defects.

25:01.533 --> 25:05.604 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: There was a case
reported in Hawaii of a baby
born with brain damage. The

25:05.604 --> 25:08.941 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
mother in that case
had lived in Brazil?

25:08.941 --> 25:13.412 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. THOMAS FRIEDEN: That's
correct. The mother had lived in
Brazil, gotten Zika in Brazil,

25:13.412 --> 25:20.753 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and then the baby, sadly, was
born with a malformation or
problems in Hawaii.

25:20.753 --> 25:26.592 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And we have seen people,
travelers coming back from areas
with Zika, with Zika in the

25:26.592 --> 25:32.498 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
U.S. We have diagnosed a dozen
so far in our laboratory. And
this is not unexpected. When

25:32.498 --> 25:38.637 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Zika is in a community, it can
spread quite widely. But what we
have seen is that it tends

25:38.637 --> 25:42.074 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to be associated with one
particular type of mosquito that
is only in certain parts

25:42.074 --> 25:44.910 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of the U.S..

25:44.910 --> 25:51.717 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And in those parts of the U.S.,
with the use of mosquito
repellent, air conditioning,
screens,

25:51.717 --> 25:56.455 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we haven't seen large-scale
transmission with viruses with
this type. But we're still
learning

25:56.455 --> 25:59.958 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
more and working hard to
learn more about this virus.

25:59.958 --> 26:04.797 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But is it not
likely to spread into the U.S.,
given the pattern so far, and

26:04.797 --> 26:07.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
as the weather warms
up come spring?

26:07.533 --> 26:11.804 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. THOMAS FRIEDEN: I don't have
a crystal ball. I can't predict
what will happen.

26:11.804 --> 26:17.009 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I can tell you what has happened
with other similar viruses. This
is spread by the mosquito

26:17.009 --> 26:22.748 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that spreads the dengue virus.
And there are some parts of
Florida and potentially some

26:22.748 --> 26:27.085 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
parts of Texas where we have
seen transmission of that virus,
so it's possible that that

26:27.085 --> 26:29.755 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
will occur.

26:29.755 --> 26:36.061 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
However, this virus is a little
different, in that it mostly
affects people, and so -- and

26:36.061 --> 26:41.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
people only carry it for a few
days. So how widely it will
spread in an area where you're

26:41.667 --> 26:45.604 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not seeing people without air
conditioning, you're not seeing
people otherwise, we don't

26:45.604 --> 26:48.140 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
know.

26:48.140 --> 26:53.879 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it is certainly possible
that we will see cases in
certain parts of the U.S. and

26:53.879 --> 26:59.618 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
possible we might even see
clusters. But we don't predict
that we would see something

26:59.618 --> 27:03.355 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
widespread, as we saw, for
example, with West Nile virus,
where you have a bird reservoir

27:03.355 --> 27:06.792 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
which can spread it
and perpetuate it.

27:06.792 --> 27:12.064 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we can't say for sure. What
we can say for sure is that, if
you're pregnant, you

27:12.064 --> 27:17.870 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
would think twice before you go
to a place with Zika. We advise
you not to. And for anyone

27:17.870 --> 27:23.575 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who is in a place with Zika or
other mosquito-borne diseases,
you can take practical steps to

27:23.575 --> 27:28.447 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
greatly reduce your risk of
getting a mosquito bite, and
therefore a disease spread by
mosquitoes.

27:28.447 --> 27:30.682 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, Dr.
Thomas Frieden of the CDC, thank
you so much.

27:30.682 --> 27:32.851 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DR. THOMAS FRIEDEN: Thank you.

27:32.851 --> 27:39.358 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: The CDC also
launched its latest anti-smoking
campaign this week. We spoke

27:39.358 --> 27:45.597 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with Dr. Frieden about its
